                <head>Married</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>Let sad ambition rashly try To break the bands our Union tie-- It strives
                    in vain--while here we see The North and South in heart agree, The patriot's
                    love and Cupid's power Still rule the court and rule the bower: Firm and united,
                    heart and hand, The Union's safe in Hymen's hand.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
